						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">unregistered wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Ok, I'm not rounding up... so I have 12.5... which is 12.  12 * 16 = 192... or $C0.  But that $C0 doesn't make since because my character is standing on row $A0.  I added 2 (32) to 10.5 to get the value at her feet. ...  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /> ... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /> (mad at myself cause I'm still confused)</div><br /><br />She is 32 pixels tall, right? Her position (oY) is where the top of her head is right?<br /><br />So if her head is at $A0, Her feet are at $C0. If her head is at $C0, her feet are at $E0. There's nothing more to it.<br /><br />If you want what row her head is on, don't add the 32 to oY. If you want what row her feet are on, add the 32 to oY. I get the impression you're overthinking this.</div>

					
