				<table cellspacing="4" align="center" width="150">
			
				<tr>
					<td><img src="./styles/subsilver2/imageset/en/icon_user_offline.gif" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /></td>
				</tr>
			
				<tr>
					<td><img src="./download/file.php?avatar=3504.gif" width="48" height="48" alt="User avatar" /></td>
				</tr>
			
				</table>

				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Wed Apr 02, 2008 2:09 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 1174
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">00 gives you 00<br />01 gives you 02<br />02 gives you 04<br />03 gives you 06. Etc. This is what you want. <br /><br />So it's doubled because rows are 32 bytes long. You have what row she's standing on.<br /><br />Multiply it by two. The carry is clear if you're reading from $0600 and set if you're reading from $0700.<br /><br />Say $00 is the row. ASL. Result is $00, Carry clear. You want $0600.<br />Say $20 is the row. ASL. Result is $40, Carry clear. You want $0640.<br /><br />Say $80 is the row. ASL. Result is $00, Carry set. You want $0700.<br />Say $A0 is the row. ASL. Result is $40, Carry set. You want $0740.<br /><br />Once you've got the row, multiply it by two, transfer that result to y and branch to either a read from $0600,y or $0700,y depending on the carry. <br /><br />It's all input output. Write out what you want like you did. Find the pattern that can make it happen.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://kasumi.itch.io/indivisible">https://kasumi.itch.io/indivisible</a><!-- m --></div>
