					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">unregistered wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Does asm6, my assembler, automatically cut off the top and bottom 8 pixels of the screen?</div><br />Like 3gengames said, the assembler has absolutely nothing to do with this. The assembler only translates written code into instructions for the CPU, and it never tells the system to do anything other than what you have specified in the source code. The assembler doesn't even know what system will run the binary it outputs (only that the CPu is a 6502!), so it can't possibly do anything that's specific to the NES.<br /><br />That being said, a lot of emulators are configured to hide those scanlines, because a lot of TVs cut a part of the picture. All emulators should allow you to change this configuration in the video settings.</div>

