			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">SMB1 has 32 lines of status bar and 208 lines of playfield, organized as 13 rows each 16 pixels tall. In land and underground levels, the bottom two rows of metatiles, or 32 pixels, are normally filled with the cracked blocks.<br /><br />So the screen is divided as follows:<br />0-31: Status<br />32-207: Playfield above ground level<br />208-239: Ground level and below<br /><br />SMB1 (for Super Mario All-Stars) uses a 224-line screen mode, where only 208-223 are ground.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
